<body>
<h1>Menu and Toolbar Items</h1>
Commands to operate the puzzle are available from the Sudoku view menu,
the toolbar, and through keystrokes. Note, the actions are enabled or
disabled according to the state of the puzzle. So, for example, you can
only lock input values when you have values entered and solve the
puzzle only when you have locked the input values.<br>
<h2>Menu Items</h2>
Menu items are available from the Sudoku view menu by clicking on the
menu button (the triangle to the right of the <span
 style="font-weight: bold;">Solve Puzzle</span> button).<br>
<img alt="View Menu" title="View Menu" src="../images/viewmenu.gif"
 style="width: 211px; height: 120px;"><br>
<br>
<span style="font-weight: bold;">New Puzzle</span> - terminate this
puzzle and start a new one.<br>
<span style="font-weight: bold;">Lock Inputs</span> - lock the cells
with values as the input cells. You much have value(s) entered first.
This enables the <span style="font-weight: bold;">Hint</span> and <span
 style="font-weight: bold;">Solve Puzzle</span> items.<br>
<span style="font-weight: bold;">Hint </span>- fill in the selected
cell with the value from the solution.<br>
<span style="font-weight: bold;">Solve Puzzle</span> - fill in the
entire puzzle with the solution.<br>
<h2>Toolbar Items</h2>
<img alt="New Puzzle" title="New Puzzle" src="../images/new_wiz.png"
 style="width: 16px; height: 16px;"> -
<span style="font-weight: bold;">New Puzzle</span><br>
<img alt="Lock Inputs" title="Lock Inputs" src="../images/lock.png"
 style="width: 16px; height: 16px;"> -
<span style="font-weight: bold;">Lock Inputs</span><br>
<img alt="Hint" title="Hint" src="../images/help.png"
 style="width: 16px; height: 16px;"> -
<span style="font-weight: bold;">Hint</span><br>
<img alt="Solve Puzzle" title="Solve Puzzle"
 src="../images/calculator.png" style="width: 16px; height: 16px;"> -
<span style="font-weight: bold;">Solve Puzzle</span><br>
<h2>Keystrokes</h2>
For quicker action, instead of using one of the menu or toolbar items,
you can affect a command with its assigned keystroke.<br>
"N" - <span style="font-weight: bold;">New Puzzle</span><br>
"L" - <span style="font-weight: bold;">Lock Inputs</span><br>
"H" - <span style="font-weight: bold;">Hint</span><br>
"S" - <span style="font-weight: bold;">Solve Puzzle<br>
<br>
</span>
